            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Yes, the Science Mission Directorate is an existing program and has been funded in previous fiscal years.\n* Most recently, the Science account was funded at $7,250,000,000 in the FY 2026 enacted bill (H.R. 6938).",
            "rationale": "Confirms the program's existing status and provides the most recent enacted funding level as a baseline.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1577321342:a05a5dc5c346",
            "label": "Brief Description of and Justification For the Request",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Request $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate to restore program stability and ensure U.S. leadership in the face of rising international competition.\n* NASA Science delivers outsized returns in discovery and national prestige, returning approximately $3 to the economy for every $1 invested.\n* Funding supports a highly skilled workforce and provides a steady demand for cutting-edge R&D from over 4,000 civil servants and thousands of contractors.\n* This request aligns with nonpartisan National Academies Decadal Survey priorities, providing the most rigorous basis for federal investment in space exploration.",
            "rationale": "Weaves together economic impact, workforce stability, international competition, and decadal survey priorities from the advocacy talking points.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_312776735:407c6c8047ca",
            "label": "How Does This Request Affect NY-02 and/or the State of New York? Please Be Specific.",
            "help_text": "Detail the local or statewide impact of this appropriation.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science funding directly supports the NY-02 industrial base, with over $200,000 in recent contracts awarded to specialized local firms.\n* Key recipients include Raith America Inc ($78,125), Schenck Corp ($57,627), and PLX Inc. ($46,995), supporting high-tech manufacturing and engineering jobs in the district.\n* Sustained investment ensures that the local aerospace supply chain remains competitive and capable of supporting national missions and scientific discovery.",
